    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey can u explain why my muscles feel like they're burning when i do sprints? like what's actually happening biologically when that stinging feeling starts?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "When you experience the burning sensation in your muscles during sprints, it's primarily caused by an increase in lactic acid production. Lactic acid is a byproduct of anaerobic metabolism, where your body breaks down glucose without enough oxygen. As your muscles contract rapidly during sprinting, they rely on anaerobic glycolysis, leading to the buildup of lactic acid, which irritates nerve endings and causes pain. This sensation is often referred to as \" delayed onset muscle soreness\" (DOMS).",
      "source": "target",
